---
const faqs = [
  {
    question: 'Will the chemical peel hurt or cause significant discomfort?',
    answer_html: "<p>Most clients feel only a mild tingling or warm sensation during a chemical peel, which fades quickly. The intensity depends on the peel strength, and our team monitors your skin throughout to keep you comfortable. Deeper peels may feel slightly more noticeable, and we will explain what to expect before we begin.</p>",
  },
  {
    question: 'How often can I get chemical peels and when will I see results?',
    answer_html: "<p>Many clients notice smoother, brighter skin within a few days, with continued improvement over the following weeks. For ongoing results, lighter peels are often repeated every few weeks, while stronger peels are spaced further apart. We will recommend a schedule based on your skin and goals during your consultation.</p>",
  },
  {
    question: "Who shouldn't get chemical peels?",
    answer_html: "<p>Chemical peels may not be appropriate if you are pregnant or breastfeeding, have an active skin infection or open wound in the treatment area, or are using certain medications. During your consultation we review your skin and health history to confirm a peel is a safe and suitable option for you.</p>",
  },
  {
    question: 'How is this different from at-home peels or facials?',
    answer_html: "<p>Professional peels use medical-grade formulas at carefully controlled strengths, applied and monitored by trained providers. This allows for deeper, more targeted results than most at-home products, while keeping the treatment safe and tailored to your skin type and concerns.</p>",
  },
];
---

<section class="section cpf-s8">
  <div class="container--narrow">

    <h2 class="cpf-s8__heading">Frequently asked questions</h2>

    <div class="cpf-s8__faq">

      {faqs.map((faq) => (
        <details class="cpf-s8__item">
          <summary class="cpf-s8__question">{faq.question}</summary>
          <div class="cpf-s8__answer" set:html={faq.answer_html} />
        </details>
      ))}

    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .cpf-s8 .container--narrow {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .cpf-s8__heading {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-h2);
    font-weight: var(--weight-regular);
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.3;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .cpf-s8__faq {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
  }

  .cpf-s8__item {
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
  }

  .cpf-s8__item[open] .cpf-s8__question {
    font-weight: var(--weight-bold);
  }

  .cpf-s8__question {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    padding: var(--space-sm) 0;
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    font-weight: var(--weight-regular);
    color: var(--color-text);
    cursor: pointer;
    list-style: none;
    line-height: 1.5;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .cpf-s8__question::-webkit-details-marker {
    display: none;
  }

  .cpf-s8__question::after {
    content: '+';
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    font-weight: var(--weight-regular);
    flex-shrink: 0;
    line-height: 1;
    color: var(--color-text);
    opacity: 0.6;
  }

  .cpf-s8__item[open] .cpf-s8__question::after {
    content: '\2212';
  }

  .cpf-s8__answer {
    padding: 0 0 var(--space-sm);
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .cpf-s8__answer p {
    margin: 0 0 0.75em;
  }

  .cpf-s8__answer p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }
</style>
